HEADWORD: Cheviot
<hw>Chev"i*ot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
valuable breed of mountain sheep in Scotland, which takes its name from
the Cheviot hills.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A woolen fabric, for men's clothing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chevisance</ent>⟦br⟧
